President Obama has appointed Dr. Mary Wakefield as the Administrator of the Health Resources and Services Administration (HRSA). Dr. Wakefield, a top rural health care professional, will oversee the agency responsible for delivering health care to the uninsured and underserved. Her expertise in rural health care and public policy will be instrumental in expanding and improving services for those in need. HRSA manages programs that bring health care providers to underserved areas and will also administer $2.5 billion allocated in the Recovery Act for health care infrastructure and professional training. Dr. Wakefield has an extensive background in health policy and has served in various leadership positions in the health care industry. She holds a Ph.D. in nursing and has received numerous awards for her contributions to the field.